  "prompt": "Railways SSE put under group C where all Central govt gives group B status for grade pay 4600?",
  "response": "In Indian Railways, the designation of posts and the corresponding classification into Groups A, B, and C are based on the level of responsibility and the nature of the work. The Group B status typically applies to certain posts that involve significant responsibilities and are often filled by promotion from Group C posts or through direct recruitment.\n\nHowever, the exact classification and status of specific positions, such as the Senior Section Engineer (SSE) in Railways, can vary based on government orders, pay commission recommendations, and departmental regulations. As of my last update, the SSE position typically falls under Group C, but it has been a topic of discussion regarding whether it should be elevated to Group B status due to the responsibilities carried by SSEs.\n\nIf there have been recent developments or changes in this classification due to government directives, announcements, or recommendations from pay commissions since my last update, I would recommend checking with the latest official notifications from the Indian Railways or the Ministry of Railways for the most accurate and up-to-date information.",
